1
00:00:02,960 --> 00:00:05,040
(PHONE RINGING)

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,840
-DANNY: Clara?
-CLARA: Shut up.

3
00:00:07,920 --> 00:00:11,240
-Is that how we communicate now?
-Shut up, shut up! Shut up!

4
00:00:11,320 --> 00:00:12,320
I need to talk to you!

5
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,080
All right, well I'll be there
in a couple of minutes, so...

6
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:16,680
-No, not while you're in the room!
-Stupid me. The very idea!

7
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:18,440
-Shut up!
-Okay.

8
00:00:18,520 --> 00:00:20,720
-Stay, shut up!
-(LAUGHS) Okay.

9
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:23,520
Things to say. Not all of them good.

10
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,600
Wouldn't it be better if
I was actually there?

11
00:00:25,680 --> 00:00:28,040
Oh, Danny, everything is better when
you're here, but maybe...

12
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:30,280
Maybe not this.

13
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Okay.

14
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:39,840
Um...

15
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:43,240
Okay, before all of that.

16
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:45,640
Before all of the stuff
that I did wrong.

17
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,000
I love you.

18
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:53,480
I love you.

19
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:55,800
No, not like that. Not like
it's automatic. Not like it's

20
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:58,320
how you end the phone call,
the sign off, the pat on the back.

21
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,720
-Clara?
-Danny, I'll never say

22
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:02,160
those words again.
Not to anybody else, ever.

23
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:05,440
Those words, from me, are yours now.

24
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:17,840
So, erm...

25
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:20,520
That's a thing.

26
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:24,960
Okay? Danny?

27
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:32,240
Erm... There's more,
but that's kind of the headline.

28
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:35,160
Okay, Danny? Please speak
to me, this is killing me.

29
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:41,640
Danny, I love you,

30
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:45,360
and you are the last person
who is ever going to hear me say that.

31
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:51,040
WOMAN: Hello?
Hello, is someone there?

32
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:54,000
Hello, er... Yeah, who is this?

33
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:56,040
WOMAN: I just picked up the phone,
I'm sorry.

34
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:59,560
-I found it.
-Oh, okay, uh...

35
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:01,760
Could you please just put me back on
the phone to Danny,

36
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:03,720
I was talking to Danny.

37
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:06,160
Sorry. I'm so sorry!

38
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:08,880
Okay, what are you sorry about?

39
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,240
Could you please just
pass phone back to...

40
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:13,360
WOMAN: He was crossing the road,
I found the phone.

41
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,120
It must have just got thrown...

42
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:18,560
The car, it just came out of nowhere.

43
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:19,760
I'm so sorry.

44
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:22,240
(SIRENS BLARING)

45
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,760
(SIRENS BLARING)

46
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,880
(PANTING)

47
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:58,280
MAN: By now, I'm sure that you've
heard the rumours,

48
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:01,640
and it is with great sadness that
I must confirm them to be true.

49
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:05,320
I have gathered you all
here today to say that Mr Pink,

50
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:08,440
Danny Pink, has sadly passed away.

51
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:11,360
I'm sure you'll all join me in wishing
his family and friends

52
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:13,480
our sincerest condolences.

53
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,320
Mr Pink was an inspiration
to all of those who knew him.

54
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:21,160
A soldier, a teacher, a friend. It was
no secret that he had a close

55
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:25,560
relationship with Miss Oswald, and our
thoughts and prayers are with her too.

56
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,720
(PHONE RINGING)

57
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:31,240
(RINGING CONTINUES)

58
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,800
(PHONE RINGING)

59
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:44,840
Hello, love. You all right?

60
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,520
Of course you're not.

61
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:54,560
Sorry, of course you're not all right.

62
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:00,360
You know what you should do?
You should cry. Let go.

63
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,200
Of what?

64
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:08,400
It's a terrible thing.
Just a terrible, terrible thing.

65
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:11,600
-It wasn't terrible.
-Clara?

66
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:13,920
It was boring.

67
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:15,800
Boring?

68
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,040
It was ordinary.

69
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:22,120
(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

70
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,800
People just kept walking,

71
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:27,560
with their iPods
and their shopping bags.

72
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:30,560
He was alive, and then he was dead,
and it was nothing.

73
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:32,360
Like stepping off a bus.

74
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:35,000
He deserved better. And so did you.

75
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:37,560
I don't deserve anything.
Nobody deserves anything.

76
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:42,120
But I am owed better.

77
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:44,960
I am owed.

78
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,160
Who owes you?

79
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:51,560
DOCTOR: Clara! Clara?

80
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,120
Hey!

81
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:57,920
Sorry, I was busy. What's happening?

82
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,120
Oh, nothing. You know,
same old, same old.

83
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:04,200
Well, you're only human.
So what I can do for you, Clara?

84
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:10,160
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

85
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,000
(GASPS)

86
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:07,960
Clara?

87
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:13,800
-Start her up!
-Where are we going?

88
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:15,240
-Away.
-From?

89
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:18,320
-Just away.
-Normally you say work, or kids,

90
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,760
or dishes,
or dullness. What's happened?

91
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:24,280
-A volcano.
-I'm sorry?

92
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,760
I've never seen an active volcano,
do you know one?

93
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:29,840
What's so good about seeing a volcano?
It's just a sort of leaky mountain.

94
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,520
I've never seen lava.

95
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,520
It's rubbish.

96
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,600
Prove it.

97
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,960
It's on your neck.

98
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,440
Do you still have those
sleep patch things?

99
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:56,920
You can't have one.

100
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,640
-I'm having trouble sleeping.
-You still can't have one.

101
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:02,360
-Can I have one?
-No, you can't have one.

102
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:11,040
So, volcano.
What's so good about lava?

103
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:21,240
(EXPLODING)

104
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,360
(GASPS)

105
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:32,160
You told me once what it would take to
destroy a Tardis key.

106
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:36,080
That's what's so good about lava.

107
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:42,880
All seven.
From all of your hiding places.

108
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,280
Clara? What are you doing?

109
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:51,480
Don't! Be very, very careful,
with that. Those are very, very...

110
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:59,680
Do I have your attention?

111
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:02,040
-Yes.
-Good.

112
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:05,800
No. Not good, Clara.

113
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:08,480
Danny Pink.

114
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,800
Yes?

115
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:14,040
CLARA: Is dead.

116
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:18,080
And?

117
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:21,200
-Seriously?
-And.

118
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,160
And fix it.

119
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:30,120
Change it. Change what happened.

120
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:33,800
Save him. Bring him back.

121
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,040
No.

122
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:54,400
Five left. Every time you say no to me,

123
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:57,040
I will throw another key down there.
Do we understand each other?

124
00:08:57,120 --> 00:09:00,120
Well. I understand you. Let's not get
carried away.

125
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:01,600
Time can be rewritten.

126
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:05,320
With precision. With great care.

127
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:09,560
And not today.
But you know that of course,

128
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:11,960
otherwise you wouldn't
be threatening me.

129
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:13,800
Did you just say no?

130
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:18,960
If I change the events
that brought you here,

131
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:22,040
you will never come here and ask
me to change those events.

132
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:27,400
Paradox loop, the time
line disintegrates,

133
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:29,560
your time line. And yes.

134
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,920
-Yes?
-Yes.

135
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:38,320
I did just said no.
Throw away the key.

136
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,760
I have seen you change time.

137
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:43,200
I have seen you break
any rule you want.

138
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,280
I know when I can, and I know when
I can't. Throw the key.

139
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:47,920
I know what you're doing.
You're trying to take control.

140
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,160
I am in control. Throw away the key.
Do as you are told.

141
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,240
No!

142
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:54,800
Well, either you do as you're told,
or stop threatening me.

143
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:57,560
There really isn't a third option here.

144
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:00,520
Do you know what, Doctor?

145
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,960
When it comes to taking control,

146
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,640
you really are out of your depth.

147
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:16,640
One last chance, and I don't
care about the rules.

148
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:19,680
I don't give a damn about paradoxes.

149
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:23,480
Save Danny, bring him back, or I swear

150
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:27,040
you will never step inside
your Tardis again.

151
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:28,840
-No.
-Do as you are told.

152
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:30,400
-No.
-Say it again so I know you mean it.

153
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,760
No.

154
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:35,680
-I'm not kidding, Doctor.
-Neither am I.

155
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,760
I will do it.

156
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:39,120
No, Clara. My Clara.
I don't think you will.

157
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:01,400
I'd say I'm sorry, but I'd do it again.

158
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,520
(CLARA SOBBING)

159
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,160
CLARA: I'd do it again.

160
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:09,960
Well. What are you doing, why are you
just going to stand there?

161
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:12,440
Do you understand
what I have just done?

162
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,880
-Look in your hand.
-There's nothing in my hand.

163
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,880
-Clara, look in your hand.
-The keys, they're gone.

164
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,120
They're down there.

165
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,720
Clara, Clara, look in your hand.

166
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:28,160
-There's nothing in my hand.
-Yes. Yes, there is, look.

167
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:37,480
Did you seriously think that
that was gonna work on me?

168
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:51,760
They're not sleep patches,
they induce a dream state.

169
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,920
Makes you very suggestible.

170
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:06,560
I allowed the whole scenario
to play out just as you planned.

171
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:09,920
I was curious about how
far you would go.

172
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:16,800
-Well. Now you know.
-Yeah, now I know.

173
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:20,720
I love him.

174
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:26,600
Yes, you're quite the mess
of chemicals, aren't you?

175
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,320
So, what now?

176
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:36,960
What do we do now? You and me,
what happens now?

177
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:41,920
Doctor?

178
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:46,680
Go to hell.

179
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:52,880
Fair enough.

180
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,840
Absolutely, fair enough.

181
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:07,520
Clara?

182
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:14,080
You asked me what we're going to do.
I told you. We're going to hell.

183
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,960
Or wherever it is people go
when they die.

184
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:20,120
If there is anywhere. Wherever it
is, we're going there,

185
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,880
and we're going to find Danny.

186
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,880
And if it is in any way possible,
we are going to bring him home.

187
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:36,360
Almost every culture in the universe
has some concept of an afterlife.

188
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:39,760
I always meant to have a
look around, see if I can find one.

189
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:43,560
-You're going to help me?
-Well, why wouldn't I help you?

190
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:46,600
-Because of what I did. I just tried...
-You betrayed me.

191
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,880
You betrayed my trust,
you betrayed our friendship,

192
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:53,200
you betrayed everything
that I've ever stood for.

193
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:54,400
You let me down!

194
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,800
Then why are you helping me?

195
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:00,640
Why?

196
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,560
Do you think I care for you so
little, that betraying me

197
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,000
would make a difference?

198
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:14,200
Stop it with the eyes.
Don't do that with the eyes.

199
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:16,040
How do you do that anyway,

200
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:18,040
it's like they inflate!

201
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:26,560
And cut out the whining
while you're at it.

202
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:30,960
We've got work to do. This is
it, Clara, one of those moments.

203
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:34,920
-What moments?
-The darkest day, the blackest hour.

204
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:40,360
Chin up, shoulders back, let's see what
we're made of, you and I.

205
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:49,480
Switching off the safeguards.

206
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:51,200
Turning off the nav-com.

207
00:14:51,280 --> 00:14:52,360
Remember we did this before?

208
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:54,960
We plugged you into the
Tardis telepathic interface.

209
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:56,720
We ended up all over
Danny's time stream.

210
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:59,120
Because you and he are linked,
strongly linked.

211
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,560
Your time streams are intertwined.

212
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:02,840
So if he's anywhere at all, that
link will hold. Give me your hands.

213
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:05,320
-Doctor...
-We're in a hurry.

214
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:06,920
I don't deserve a friend like you.

215
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,360
Clara, I'm terribly sorry, but I am
exactly what you deserve.

216
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:13,600
Think about Danny.

217
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:15,400
Think about the man you lost.

218
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:19,200
Let it hurt. Let it burn.
But don't bleat.

219
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:22,720
Don't ask, why him? Why me?

220
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:25,760
Forget all that. Ask one question.
Just one.

221
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:29,600
Ask, where is Danny Pink now?
Where is he now?

222
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:41,320
(MACHINE CLANGING)

223
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:48,120
Well! The Tardis thinks he's somewhere.

224
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:10,160
Has anyone offered you a coffee?

225
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,320
Um...

226
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,240
Well, no...

227
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:18,160
Could we have some coffee along here
please? The good kind,

228
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:19,520
we've got a new one.

229
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:22,920
Five minutes, tops.

230
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:24,480
Best to wait for the good coffee.

231
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:26,560
Where am I?

232
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:28,440
Because sometimes, it's just the
instant, and oh...

233
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:32,040
-Where am I?
-Well. Big question.

234
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:34,000
We try to take that one slowly.

235
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:36,520
We have been trying to
contact family members,

236
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:40,000
but really, there's so much admin...

237
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,480
I wasn't here, I was...

238
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:49,920
Yeah. That last thing
that happened to you.

239
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:54,640
It really happened, I'm afraid.
But that's life.

240
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:57,080
Well! Not life, I suppose.

241
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:01,520
There are some forms to fill in.
They might help you relax.

242
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:05,480
Well, they won't,
but we do need them filled in.

243
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:07,880
Right, important thing. Need to know.

244
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:10,160
Are you being cremated?

245
00:17:11,040 --> 00:17:13,640
Sorry, it's a fairly urgent question.

246
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:16,640
I don't know. Never really
thought about it.

247
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:18,080
I'm going to put you down as a 'yes',

248
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:20,040
that's pretty much
the default these days.

249
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:23,520
-God, if people only knew...
-Only knew what?

250
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:27,320
We've got a burner in No. 12,
tell them to prep please.

251
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:29,920
-A burner?
-Yeah, it's fine, we'll come to that.

252
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,480
I don't understand where I am.

253
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:36,880
(GASPS)

254
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:50,960
Oh! Look at that!

255
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:53,080
You can see my house from here!

256
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:56,560
Yeah, sorry, probably not helping.

257
00:17:57,480 --> 00:17:58,480
Where am I?

258
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:02,560
Um. You sort of know, don't you?

259
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:06,280
Most people kind of know, it's just hard
to get traction on the concept.

260
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:07,800
Where am I?

261
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:12,800
Okay. You're dead.
And this is what's next.

262
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,800
I'm not dead! How can I be dead?

263
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:16,480
Our sincere condolences.

264
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:19,280
-I'm standing right here!
-Yes, you are.

265
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:21,040
Welcome to the Underworld.

266
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:24,520
Otherwise known as the Nethersphere,
or the Promised Land.

267
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:28,120
It's where you go when you die.

268
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:31,160
(GASPS)

269
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:39,480
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

270
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:42,760
Would you like to breathe into a bag?

271
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:52,320
Where are we?

272
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:55,280
Nav-com's offline, we'll have to do
this old school.

273
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:56,520
But this is where Danny is?

274
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:59,920
Almost certainly not. It's where
there's a connection with Danny.

275
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,080
According to the Tardis, this is
where it's most likely

276
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:05,600
that your timeline will re-intersect
with his, and that won't do.

277
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:07,080
-What won't?
-You won't, look at you.

278
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:10,240
I need sceptical, clever,
critical. I don't need mopy.

279
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:12,800
It puts years on your face.
What if people see us together?

280
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:15,520
-You look like you've been melted.
-Are you forgetting why we're here?

281
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:18,560
We're here to get your boyfriend back
from the dead,

282
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:21,040
so buck up and give me some attitude.

283
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,720
CLARA: Fish tanks?

284
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:47,480
In a mausoleum?

285
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:06,400
-What does that mean?
-It means those are

286
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:08,120
definitely not fish tanks.

287
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:22,720
-Why?
-I don't know.

288
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:35,640
Okay. I'm assuming they didn't
actually drown in there.

289
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:43,440
No. They were placed, after death.

290
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:46,720
These are tombs.

291
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:50,800
Water tombs, some sort of fluid, anyway.

292
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:53,360
-With chairs?
-With chairs, yes.

293
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:57,080
Extra comfort for the deceased.
It pays to die rich.

294
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:02,720
Oh, God.

295
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:10,680
Am I going to find Danny now?
Is that why the Tardis brought us here?

296
00:21:10,760 --> 00:21:12,680
-I don't want to see him like that.
-Good point.

297
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:16,040
Tombs with windows!
Who wants to watch their loved ones rot?

298
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:19,120
Why would anyone go to so much trouble

299
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:22,800
just to keep watch on the dead?

300
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,200
(CRACKING)

301
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:34,440
(WHOOSHING)

302
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,240
WOMAN: 3.

303
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:44,200
Death is not an end.

304
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:46,520
But we can we help with that.

305
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:51,080
Ever since 3W encountered the truth
about the death experience,

306
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:54,840
we have been working hard to
find a better life for the deceased.

307
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:59,480
At 3W, afterlife means after-care.

308
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:02,120
Okay. Bit strange?

309
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:04,520
Very.

310
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:07,720
Why have the scrolling
and a voice?

311
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:10,880
-Is it difficult?
-Is what difficult?

312
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:13,120
Reading all those words back to front?

313
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:19,160
Come on. We've come a long way.

314
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,680
Hello. I hope you are well.

315
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,160
How may I assist you with your death?

316
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:30,640
Well, there is er... No immediate hurry.

317
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:33,280
We're just, er... We're just...

318
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:34,880
(STUTTERING)

319
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:37,920
-Browsing.
-Yeah, yeah, browsing.

320
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:41,360
Please take all the time you need.

321
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:44,880
At 3W, you always have the rest
of your life.

322
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:48,120
Oh, good. That's good to know,
isn't that good, Clara?

323
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:49,280
Yeah. Great.

324
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:51,920
-Exactly what is 3W?
-Apologies.

325
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:56,080
Clearly you have not received
the official 3W greetings package.

326
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:58,880
Well, no, it's just an unexpected...

327
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:17,400
(EXHALES)

328
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:18,960
(GASPS)

329
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:22,080
Welcome to the 3W Institute.

330
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:26,320
Clara, is it over now?

331
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,480
I think it's over, yeah.

332
00:23:30,120 --> 00:23:32,960
You also have not received the official
welcome package...

333
00:23:33,040 --> 00:23:35,120
Oh, I'm good, thanks, no worries!

334
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:38,000
-Who are you?
-I am Missy.

335
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:41,480
-Missy?
-Mobile Intelligent Systems Interface.

336
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:44,760
I am a multi-function, interactive,
welcome-droid,

337
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:48,200
helping you, to help me, to help you.

338
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,160
You're very...

339
00:23:53,280 --> 00:23:54,400
...realistic.

340
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:55,800
-Tongues?
-Shut up.

341
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:58,840
I am fully programmed
with social interaction norms

342
00:23:58,920 --> 00:24:01,120
appropriate to a range of visitors.

343
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:04,360
Please indicate if you'd like me
to adjust my intimacy settings.

344
00:24:04,560 --> 00:24:07,040
Oh, yes, please, please, do that,
do that now right now, yes.

345
00:24:07,360 --> 00:24:08,640
Maybe just a tad, yeah.

346
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,040
I need to speak to
whoever's in charge here.

347
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,640
I am in charge.

348
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,600
Well, who's in charge of you?

349
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:17,080
I am in charge of me.

350
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:19,480
Well, who repairs you?
Who... Who... Who maintains you?

351
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:21,480
I am programmed for self-repair.

352
00:24:22,080 --> 00:24:23,960
I am maintained by my heart.

353
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:26,960
(GASPS)

354
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:29,360
MISSY: Is everything in order?

355
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:32,960
Who maintains your heart?

356
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:36,560
My heart is maintained by the Doctor.

357
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:39,680
Doctor who?

358
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:42,960
Dr Chang!

359
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:46,920
CHANG: Who's there?

360
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:51,040
-Hello?
-Hello.

361
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,920
DOCTOR: Hello.

362
00:24:55,240 --> 00:24:56,880
You can probably take your hand
down now, Doctor.

363
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,240
So. Hey. Condolences.

364
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,280
Condolences?

365
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:09,280
CHANG: It's a mausoleum. It's our hello.

366
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:11,640
Is there a particular dead person
you want to talk to?

367
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:16,040
-(VOICES WHISPERING)
-Yes.

368
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:18,360
Yes, there is.

369
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:19,960
This way then?

370
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:21,600
Are you okay?

371
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,440
No.

372
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:26,840
Good. There would be
something very wrong if you were.

373
00:25:40,760 --> 00:25:42,440
(LAUGHS)

374
00:25:49,040 --> 00:25:51,240
(SIRENS WAILING)

375
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:53,360
(HORNS HONKING)

376
00:25:56,280 --> 00:25:57,800
A bit of fresh air will do you good.

377
00:25:58,320 --> 00:25:59,520
DANNY: Why's it so cold here?

378
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,360
SEB: And the Wi-Fi's better out here.
Don't know why.

379
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:04,800
-Wi-Fi?
-Still a bit spotty, but basically...

380
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:07,880
You have Wi-Fi here? You...

381
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:10,200
You have iPads in the afterlife?

382
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:13,400
iPads? We have Steve Jobs!

383
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:17,760
Listen, erm, another big question,
for you.

384
00:26:18,280 --> 00:26:20,880
Have you ever killed anybody?

385
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:26,440
This is surreal.

386
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:33,040
Imagine embryos had telephones.

387
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:35,760
-Really not helping.
-Go with me. Go with me.

388
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:38,600
Imagine babies in wombs could talk to
other babies

389
00:26:38,960 --> 00:26:40,320
in other wombs. What would they say?

390
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:44,000
What would they think life was like,
if they could talk among themselves.

391
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,200
I really... I really have no idea.

392
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:48,520
They'd think that life
was nine months long.

393
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:52,640
And then boom, a trapdoor opens,
out you fall, gone forever.

394
00:26:53,040 --> 00:26:54,640
Never hear from those guys again.

395
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:56,360
Nothing at the end of the cord.

396
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:58,640
Okay.

397
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:01,000
This isn't really an afterlife.

398
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:05,040
It's just more life
than you were expecting.

399
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:08,920
Why did you ask me if I'd killed anyone?

400
00:27:09,560 --> 00:27:12,360
Before you were a teacher, you spent
some time as a soldier.

401
00:27:13,520 --> 00:27:14,880
Yes. So?

402
00:27:15,280 --> 00:27:18,200
Any regrets? Bad memories?

403
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:20,480
Is that any of your business?

404
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:21,880
Yes.

405
00:27:23,080 --> 00:27:24,600
(GUNS FIRING)

406
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:26,560
SOLDIER: Take cover, take cover...

407
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:27,760
Now!

408
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,920
Sorry if I triggered something.

409
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:34,320
Memory flashes can be very
impactful in the early stages...

410
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:36,600
Why?

411
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:38,320
Why what?

412
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:45,480
(GUNS FIRING)

413
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:48,240
DANNY: Why is it any of your business?

414
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:50,960
We've had a request to meet you.

415
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:53,000
Any idea who that would be from?

416
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:04,760
It's been given a priority,
that usually means...

417
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:06,280
Means what?

418
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:11,440
Well, anyway...
Erm, we've arranged a meet-up.

419
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:15,920
-When?
-Come in.

420
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:21,040
SOLDIER: Seize target!

421
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:22,880
Repeat, seize target!

422
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:28,360
SOLDIER: Danny...
Repeat, is the building secure?

423
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:30,720
SEB: So I guess you remember him, yeah?

424
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:33,200
SOLDIER: Danny, Danny?

425
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:39,600
Come in, come in.

426
00:28:41,280 --> 00:28:42,760
Going to need to take a reading off you.

427
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:44,080
A reading?

428
00:28:44,560 --> 00:28:45,720
It won't hurt.

429
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:47,000
What won't?

430
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:48,960
How does the body keep its integrity?

431
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:51,880
Why isn't it just a bunch of bones,
floating about?

432
00:28:52,240 --> 00:28:54,480
Each body is encased
in a support exoskeleton.

433
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:57,000
CLARA: An invisible exoskeleton?

434
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:58,960
CHANG: It's only invisible in the water,

435
00:28:59,040 --> 00:29:01,280
there's a specially engineered
refraction index in the fluid,

436
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:05,080
so we can see the tank resident,
unimpeded by the support mechanisms.

437
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:07,840
DOCTOR: So each skeleton
is inside something.

438
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,560
(LAUGHS)

439
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:12,480
(RUMBLING)

440
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:18,280
Are you serious? X-Ray water?

441
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:21,400
It's so cool! Look at this!

442
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:26,360
We call it dark water.

443
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:34,680
Only organic matter
can be seen through it.

444
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:41,000
I keep saying they should
use this stuff in swimming pools.

445
00:29:41,520 --> 00:29:43,600
-Why?
-Think about it.

446
00:29:44,560 --> 00:29:46,440
I am thinking about it. Why?

447
00:29:48,280 --> 00:29:49,480
Doesn't matter.

448
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:52,040
3W. What kind of name is that?
What does it mean?

449
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:54,600
Well. You know, don't you?
You're here on business,

450
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:56,560
or they wouldn't have let you in.

451
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:01,640
Sorry. Should have checked. Who are you?

452
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:03,400
I thought that you would never ask.

453
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:05,120
Sort out your security protocols,

454
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:07,440
they're a disgrace.

455
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:12,160
Another government inspection? So soon?

456
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,080
Why is there all this swearing?

457
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:17,520
Oh, I've got a lot of, erm,
internalised anger.

458
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:20,440
What does 3W stand for?

459
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:22,320
Well. The three words.

460
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:24,440
What three words?

461
00:30:25,120 --> 00:30:26,360
Seriously? You don't know?

462
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:29,360
Never mind what we know, and what we
don't know, just answer our question.

463
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:32,320
Because people who don't know,
when they hear about this,

464
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:33,440
they can freak out.

465
00:30:33,520 --> 00:30:35,080
We're not going to freak out.

466
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:38,040
If you've had a recent loss.
This might be...

467
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:41,440
This will be disturbing.

468
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:44,480
She'll be fine.

469
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:46,440
Speak for me again,
I'll detach something from you.

470
00:30:47,560 --> 00:30:48,680
I'll be fine.

471
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:52,760
You know how people are scared of dying.

472
00:30:53,040 --> 00:30:55,080
Like, everybody.

473
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:58,200
DOCTOR: Of course, it's the most
fundamental fear in the universe.

474
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:01,160
They'd be a lot more scared
if they knew what it was really like...

475
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:08,440
(HORNS HONKING)

476
00:31:09,880 --> 00:31:11,280
So...

477
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:14,040
You okay?

478
00:31:19,080 --> 00:31:20,200
I'm sorry.

479
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:22,880
I just...

480
00:31:23,240 --> 00:31:24,520
Hey, hey, hey...

481
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:26,960
Hey... Hey, listen, listen.

482
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:29,440
Hey!

483
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:31,640
Probably best not, eh?

484
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:36,360
-(DOOR CLOSING)
-Doesn't speak much.

485
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:39,160
Why would he want to see me?

486
00:31:39,640 --> 00:31:41,840
(MAN SCREAMING)

487
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:43,560
What the hell is that?

488
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:45,440
Sounds like somebody
left their body to science.

489
00:31:47,040 --> 00:31:48,240
Okay. Erm...

490
00:31:49,120 --> 00:31:52,880
It's probably time to explain why
you're always feeling cold...

491
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:57,240
-(STATIC)
-White noise off the telly.

492
00:31:57,320 --> 00:31:58,560
We've all heard it.

493
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:02,560
A few years ago, Dr Skarosa,
our founder...

494
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:04,840
...did something unexpected.

495
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:10,160
He played that noise through a
translation matrix of his own devising.

496
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:13,360
This is a recording of what he heard.

497
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:18,840
(INDISTINCT VOICES)

498
00:32:20,040 --> 00:32:22,920
-Okay. People, voices.
-So what?

499
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:25,640
Over time, Dr Skarosa became convinced

500
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:28,480
these were the voices of
the recently departed.

501
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:31,720
He believed it was a
telepathic communication from the dead.

502
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:38,880
Why? Was he an idiot?

503
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:42,720
He was able to isolate some of
the voices, hear what they were saying.

504
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:45,520
So. An idiot then.

505
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:47,080
Shut up, Doctor.

506
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:50,640
What I'm about to play you, will change
your life, and not for the better.

507
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:54,920
These are the three words which
caused Dr Skarosa to set up institutes,

508
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:58,080
like this one, all over the world,
to protect the dead.

509
00:32:58,520 --> 00:33:00,880
If you'd rather not hear these words,
there's still time.

510
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:03,400
Can you just hurry up, please,
or I'll hit you with my shoe.

511
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:06,160
(SIGHS)

512
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:09,240
-(BEEPS)
-MAN: Don't cremate me...

513
00:33:09,800 --> 00:33:11,320
Don't cremate me...

514
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:15,080
There is one simple,
horrible possibility

515
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:18,240
that has never occurred to anyone,
throughout human history.

516
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:21,440
Don't cremate me... Don't cremate me...

517
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:22,680
Don't say it!

518
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:24,560
The dead remain conscious.

519
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:28,920
The dead are fully aware of everything
that is happening to them.

520
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:32,800
You see your mind is here, your soul,
whatever you want to call it,

521
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:36,080
and you're in your new body,
in your new world.

522
00:33:36,360 --> 00:33:39,960
But you're still connected to your
old body in your old world.

523
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:42,600
You're still going to feel
what it feels.

524
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:45,800
That's why I'm cold.

525
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:48,600
They're keeping you
in a cold place, yeah.

526
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:55,640
You did say you were being cremated?

527
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:59,960
-(BEEPING)
-Sorry, let me get this.

528
00:34:00,160 --> 00:34:01,920
Sorry. Sorry, are you telling me...

529
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:03,440
Wow! Oh, that's rare.

530
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:06,960
-This never happens.
-Wow, what now? What never happens?

531
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:08,600
-You've got a call.
-A call?

532
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:10,320
-From the other side.
-Meaning?

533
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:13,440
Do you know somebody
called Clara Oswald?

534
00:34:15,680 --> 00:34:17,640
Fakery. All of it.

535
00:34:17,800 --> 00:34:20,120
-(BEEPING)
-It's a con, it's a racket.

536
00:34:20,240 --> 00:34:22,480
I promise you, this is not a con.

537
00:34:23,720 --> 00:34:24,800
-(BEEPING CONTINUES)
-What's that beeping?

538
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:27,320
DOCTOR: Never mind about beeping,
who cares about beeping?

539
00:34:27,560 --> 00:34:28,840
The dead are dead!

540
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:32,120
They're not talking to you out of
your television sets, they're just gone.

541
00:34:32,280 --> 00:34:35,920
And all these poor souls, down there
in these tanks,

542
00:34:36,080 --> 00:34:38,880
I'm sorry, but they're just dead
and they're not coming back!

543
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:46,480
DANNY: Clara? Clara, are you there?

544
00:34:49,760 --> 00:34:51,240
Danny?

545
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:53,040
I can hear you. Is that you,

546
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:54,760
oh, please say it's you...

547
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:57,040
That's her! That's Clara!

548
00:34:57,200 --> 00:34:59,440
Yeah, you're really lucky,
it hardly ever happens.

549
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:01,880
(BEEPING)

550
00:35:02,560 --> 00:35:03,760
Where did she go?

551
00:35:04,680 --> 00:35:06,200
(INHALES SHARPLY)

552
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:09,480
Ah! Just lost the signal,

553
00:35:09,560 --> 00:35:11,000
but I can track it back,
I'm pretty sure...

554
00:35:11,920 --> 00:35:14,040
I don't understand. What is happening?

555
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:16,480
We've been scanning you telepathically
since you came in,

556
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:18,400
you said you wanted to speak
to someone who'd passed.

557
00:35:19,080 --> 00:35:20,720
And we've found you a match
in the Nethersphere.

558
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:23,160
This isn't possible.
The dead don't come back.

559
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:30,160
-Come on, get her back!
-Da, da, da! I'm trying!

560
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:33,480
It was him, it was his voice.

561
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:34,840
If they scanned you telepathically

562
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:37,120
they could have lifted a voice,
it could still be a fake.

563
00:35:37,320 --> 00:35:40,000
Getting him back... Very nearly!

564
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:43,560
Clara? Can you hear me?

565
00:35:43,640 --> 00:35:45,480
Yes, Danny, I can hear you.
Can you hear me?

566
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:47,720
Yeah, yeah, I can hear you.

567
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:50,720
Clara! Oh, my God, Clara!

568
00:35:50,920 --> 00:35:52,280
What do I do?

569
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:54,280
-Who are you talking to?
-Hang on, just a moment.

570
00:35:54,520 --> 00:35:57,800
Question him. Ask him questions
only he'd know the answer to. Be sure.

571
00:35:57,960 --> 00:35:59,160
You, with me.

572
00:35:59,520 --> 00:36:00,640
Where are you going?

573
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:03,240
I've got to check out those tanks,
there's something that I'm missing.

574
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:06,560
-DANNY: Clara?
-Sceptical and critical, remember?

575
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:08,840
Be strong, even if it breaks your heart.

576
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:12,640
Connection's stabilised, should be okay.

577
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,760
Who would harvest dead bodies?

578
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:18,280
I feel like I'm
missing something obvious.

579
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:25,960
Danny?

580
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:28,760
Yeah. I'm here.

581
00:36:30,040 --> 00:36:32,680
Danny, I'm so sorry, but I'm going to
have to ask you some questions.

582
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:35,400
Questions? I swear on anything it's me.

583
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:41,360
Humankind! Bring out your dead!

584
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:49,360
(RUMBLING)

585
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:03,960
Oh, my God!

586
00:37:04,680 --> 00:37:06,120
The tanks...

587
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:08,640
The tanks are activating.
They're not supposed to do that.

588
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:10,000
All your dead people are standing,

589
00:37:10,080 --> 00:37:11,600
don't you think you
skipped the headline?

590
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:13,600
Now, now, children.

591
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:15,760
Naughty, naughty!

592
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:17,960
Dr Chang,

593
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:20,200
your welcome droid
has developed a fault.

594
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:23,240
That's not a droid. That's my boss.

595
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:27,960
You know, I might have been guilty
of just a teensy, little fibette.

596
00:37:30,440 --> 00:37:31,720
Dr Chang,

597
00:37:32,360 --> 00:37:34,800
I really liked working with you.

598
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:36,600
I've enjoyed every day of it.

599
00:37:37,160 --> 00:37:38,320
-I'm sorry?
-You know,

600
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:42,240
I've even got a little photograph
of you looking so sweet,

601
00:37:42,680 --> 00:37:44,680
I'm always going to keep it, always.

602
00:37:47,720 --> 00:37:49,640
-Are you going to kill me?
-Now come on.

603
00:37:50,400 --> 00:37:52,440
Let's not dwell on horrid things.

604
00:37:52,720 --> 00:37:55,200
This is going to be
our last conversation,

605
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:57,360
and I'm the one who's going
to have to live with that.

606
00:37:57,960 --> 00:37:59,320
CHANG: Please don't kill me.

607
00:38:01,080 --> 00:38:02,280
Say something nice.

608
00:38:02,440 --> 00:38:04,000
Please, please, please. I...

609
00:38:04,160 --> 00:38:05,640
I don't want to die.

610
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:07,240
Mmm...

611
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:08,720
You're going to kill me, aren't you?

612
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:10,640
Say something nice!

613
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:12,080
Please...

614
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:13,800
Dr Chang,

615
00:38:14,320 --> 00:38:15,800
I've got all day,

616
00:38:16,160 --> 00:38:20,320
and I'm not going to kill you
until you say something nice!

617
00:38:21,720 --> 00:38:23,560
It has been an absolute pleasure
working with you

618
00:38:23,640 --> 00:38:25,280
and I truly believe that you will never

619
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:27,080
be able to find it in your heart
to murder me.

620
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:33,000
Now, I'll be with you in a moment,

621
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:36,760
just feeling a bit

622
00:38:36,840 --> 00:38:38,720
emotional at the moment.

623
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:41,960
Cybermen!

624
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:46,800
It's me. I swear.

625
00:38:46,920 --> 00:38:48,440
I swear on anything it's me.

626
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:51,720
The very first restaurant you took me
to, that first date. What was it called?

627
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:53,320
Clara, it's me!

628
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:55,160
Then what was the name of
the restaurant?

629
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:57,080
What was it?

630
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:58,880
I can't remember.

631
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:03,600
They're Cybermen, all of them!
We've got to stop them getting out!

632
00:39:03,680 --> 00:39:05,080
Now who's missing the headline?

633
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:06,920
The Nethersphere.

634
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:08,560
You know it's ever so funny,

635
00:39:08,920 --> 00:39:11,400
the people that live inside that
think they've gone to heaven.

636
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:15,280
CLARA: My birthday. When is it?

637
00:39:15,360 --> 00:39:16,800
November 23rd.

638
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:18,160
That's right, isn't it?
I got that one right.

639
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:19,880
That's pretty basic information.

640
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:24,120
Anyone could know that.
Say something only you could say.

641
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:26,120
Tell me something only Danny would know.

642
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:28,720
(EXHALES)

643
00:39:29,920 --> 00:39:32,120
DOCTOR: That's a matrix data-slice.

644
00:39:32,440 --> 00:39:33,640
A Gallifreyan hard drive.

645
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:35,600
Time Lord technology.

646
00:39:36,120 --> 00:39:39,840
Imagine you could upload
dying minds to that? Edit them.

647
00:39:40,440 --> 00:39:43,920
Rearrange them. Get rid of
all those boring emotions.

648
00:39:44,160 --> 00:39:45,640
Ready to be re-downloaded.

649
00:39:46,280 --> 00:39:48,480
Meanwhile, you upgrade the bodies.

650
00:39:50,240 --> 00:39:52,880
Upload the mind, upgrade the body.

651
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:55,840
Cybermen from cyberspace,

652
00:39:56,840 --> 00:39:58,840
now why has no-one
ever thought of that before?

653
00:39:59,760 --> 00:40:01,600
How did you get hold of
Time Lord technology?

654
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:06,120
-Who are you?
-You know who I am.

655
00:40:07,440 --> 00:40:08,720
I told you.

656
00:40:09,720 --> 00:40:10,880
You felt it.

657
00:40:11,040 --> 00:40:12,520
(GASPS)

658
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:14,320
Surely you did.

659
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:21,440
Two hearts.

660
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:23,200
And both of them yours.

661
00:40:23,640 --> 00:40:24,840
You're a Time Lord.

662
00:40:25,280 --> 00:40:27,240
Time Lady, please,

663
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:28,800
I'm old fashioned.

664
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:30,800
Which Time Lady?

665
00:40:31,520 --> 00:40:32,840
The one you abandoned, Doctor.

666
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:34,600
The one you left for dead.

667
00:40:35,120 --> 00:40:37,000
Didn't you ever think
I'd find my way back?

668
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:39,520
Clara! Clara! Clara!
I've got to get Clara!

669
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:42,280
Oh, Clara, Clara, Clara!

670
00:40:42,360 --> 00:40:44,040
I should shoot you in a jealous rage,

671
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:45,800
now, wouldn't that be sexy?

672
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:47,400
I've turned the lift off, though.

673
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:50,240
-I presume you have stairs.
-Well, I'm not a Dalek!

674
00:40:51,560 --> 00:40:53,040
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

675
00:41:01,080 --> 00:41:02,760
Oh, dear, Doctor.

676
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:05,840
Didn't you realise where you were?

677
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:08,200
(BELLS CASCADING)

678
00:41:12,800 --> 00:41:14,400
-DANNY: I love you.
-No.

679
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:16,840
No, no, no. I'm sorry, but no.
Anybody could say that.

680
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:18,720
Anybody would know to say that.

681
00:41:18,920 --> 00:41:20,480
Say something only you could tell me.

682
00:41:20,640 --> 00:41:22,400
Prove to me you are really Danny.

683
00:41:22,640 --> 00:41:25,080
-How?
-"I love you" means nothing right now.

684
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:26,680
Not till I know who's talking.

685
00:41:26,760 --> 00:41:28,800
Say something only Danny could say...

686
00:41:29,240 --> 00:41:31,040
-Clara...
-CLARA: Danny,

687
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:34,000
if that is you,

688
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:37,600
wherever you are, whatever it takes,

689
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:40,000
I will be with you again, I swear.

690
00:41:40,160 --> 00:41:42,200
No, you won't. You're not coming here.

691
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:44,760
Nothing will stop me, nothing in
the world. As soon as I know it's you.

692
00:41:44,840 --> 00:41:47,360
There's only one way to come here,
and you are not doing that.

693
00:41:47,440 --> 00:41:49,720
I'll do anything, Danny,
anything, just...

694
00:41:50,520 --> 00:41:52,440
...say something
only you could say.

695
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:53,760
Clara, you have your life!

696
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:57,080
You have your whole life to live.
You have to stay there.

697
00:41:57,600 --> 00:41:59,960
No. I have to be with Danny Pink.

698
00:42:02,880 --> 00:42:04,840
-I love you.
-Stop saying that!

699
00:42:04,920 --> 00:42:08,240
Don't say that! If you say that again,
I swear, I will switch this thing off.

700
00:42:09,640 --> 00:42:10,680
(SIGHS)

701
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:12,720
Clara?

702
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:14,840
Yes?

703
00:42:17,040 --> 00:42:18,560
I love you.

704
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:49,040
(SOBBING)

705
00:42:54,240 --> 00:42:55,480
These emotions,

706
00:42:56,560 --> 00:42:57,800
they're terribly difficult.

707
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:01,560
But, you know,
we've got a thing for that.

708
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:06,360
We can help with all these

709
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:08,360
difficult feelings.

710
00:43:12,720 --> 00:43:14,920
Just press this.

711
00:43:17,480 --> 00:43:19,080
I'll leave you to make a decision.

712
00:44:00,880 --> 00:44:02,360
Doctor!

713
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:22,000
DOCTOR: Get away from here!
All of you, run!

714
00:44:25,160 --> 00:44:27,440
Go, go, get away from here. Run away.

715
00:44:30,280 --> 00:44:32,800
Run, run! Get away from here,
all of you, now! Now!

716
00:44:32,880 --> 00:44:36,040
I'm sorry everyone,
another ranting Scotsman in the street.

717
00:44:36,160 --> 00:44:38,120
I had no idea there was a match on.

718
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:39,400
Get away, go!

719
00:44:39,640 --> 00:44:41,320
Stop shouting, love.

720
00:44:41,920 --> 00:44:43,760
Stop making a fuss, it's too late.

721
00:44:45,160 --> 00:44:48,000
All the graves of planet earth
are about to give birth!

722
00:44:55,880 --> 00:44:58,960
Do you know the key strategic weakness
of the human race?

723
00:45:00,920 --> 00:45:02,600
The dead outnumber the living!

724
00:45:05,120 --> 00:45:06,400
Who are you?

725
00:45:06,520 --> 00:45:07,880
Oh, you know who I am.

726
00:45:09,280 --> 00:45:10,480
I'm Missy.

727
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:12,560
Who's Missy?

728
00:45:13,320 --> 00:45:15,240
Oh, please, try to keep up.

729
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:18,040
Short for Mistress.

730
00:45:19,440 --> 00:45:20,560
Well!

731
00:45:21,840 --> 00:45:24,360
I couldn't very well keep calling myself

732
00:45:24,560 --> 00:45:27,120
the Master, now could I?

733
00:45:34,640 --> 00:45:36,400
(GASPS)

734
00:45:48,800 --> 00:45:51,760
-(SOBBING)
-(BEEPING)

